{{Infobox person | image = | name = Hella Joof | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1962|11|1|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Birkerød]], [[Denmark]] | death_date = | death_place = | other_names = | occupation = Actress, film director | years_active = 1990–present }}
'''Hella Joof''' (born 1 November 1962) is a Danish actress and director. She was born to a [[Danish people|Danish]] mother and an aristocratic [[The Gambia|Gambian]] father who belonged to the [[Joof family|Joof dynasty]].<ref name="www.b.dk 2004">{{cite web | title=Så snakker vi ikke neger om det! | website=www.b.dk | date=October 24, 2004 | url=https://www.b.dk/content/item/654342 | language=da | access-date=February 25, 2018}}</ref> Joof directed ''[[Shake It All About (film)|En kort en lang]]'' (2001), ''[[Oh Happy Day (film)|Oh Happy Day]]'' (2004) and ''[[Fidibus]]'' (2006). Her feature film debut ''En kort en lang'' was seen by ten percent of the Danish population, and her second feature ''Oh Happy Day'', was sold to Disney for a US remake.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dfi.dk/faktaomfilm/person/da/101392.aspx?id=101392 |title=Hella Joof |publisher=[[Danish Film Institute]] | work=Filmdatabasen |accessdate=2016-09-24}}</ref> ''Shake It All About'' was entered into the [[24th Moscow International Film Festival]].<ref name="Moscow2002">{{cite web |url=http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=2002 |title=24th Moscow International Film Festival (2002) |accessdate=2013-03-31 |work=MIFF |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130328141921/http://moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=2002 |archivedate=2013-03-28 |df=}}</ref> She has hosted ''[[Bullerfnis]]'' and other children's TV-programs, but was also the voice of the title character in the [[hardcore pornography|hardcore]] [[pornographic film]] ''[[Constance (1998 film)|Constance]]'' (1998). As an actress, Joof is best known for award-winning performances as supporting characters in such comedies as ''[[Hannibal & Jerry]]'' (1997), ''[[Den eneste ene]]'' (1999), and ''[[Humørkort-stativ-sælgerens søn]]'' (2002). Joof appears as one of the three judges in the Television Show ''[[Talent 09]]'' a Danish adaption of ''[[Britain's Got Talent]]''.
In 2016, her film ''[[Almost Perfect (2012 film)|Almost Perfect]]'' (2012, Sover Dolly på ryggen?) was aired in [[Latin America]], the [[United States]] and [[Africa]] by the TV channel [[Eurochannel]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.eurochannel.com/index.php?option=com_acymailing&ctrl=archive&lang=es&listid=15-eurochannel-team&mailid=2340-eurochannel-april-2016-eurochannel-grid-programming-highlights-africa&task=view |title=Eurochannel – April 2016 – Eurochannel Grid + Programming Highlights Africa – Eurochannel |website=Eurochannel: The European TV channel – European movies, TV series and music |language=es-ES |access-date=2016-03-07}}</ref>
